CREATE PROCEDURE infra.register ( personalName varchar(50),device_name varchar(50),user_cell varchar(30),app_name varchar(50))
select count(*) into counter from infra.devices where name = device_name ;
select 'false' as success , 'device not exists' as message;
select id into dvc_id from infra.devices where name = device_name ;
select  count(*) into counter from infra.user_devices where device_id = dvc_id and is_logged = 1 ;
update infra.user_devices set is_logged =0 where device_id = dvc_id;
select 'false' as success , 'device has a user already, try again' as message;
select count(*) into counter from infra.users where cell = user_cell ;
select 'false' as success , 'users duplicate error' as message;
insert into infra.users (personalName,guid,cell,password,createTime) values (personalName, new_guid ,user_cell ,apassword,  Now());
update infra.users set password = apassword,createTime= Now() where cell = user_cell ;
/* add new row to user rools and if other apps there give the user  register role*/
select id into user_id from  infra.users where cell =user_cell;
select a.id into app_id from infra.applications a where a.name like  app_name  ;
select  id into roleId from infra.roles where name = 'register';
select   count(*) into counter  from user_roles where  user_id =user_id and  app_id =app_id and role_id=roleId;
insert into user_roles (user_id,  app_id, role_id ) values(user_id,app_id,roleId);
/*in any case update all users app ther register rool if they ar free user*/
select  id into freeuserId from infra.roles where name = 'freeuser';
update user_roles set role_id=roleId  where user_id= user_id and role_id= freeuserId;
select 'true' as success , 'new user was registered' as message,apassword as password    ;

CREATE PROCEDURE infra.security ( device_name varchar(100),app_name varchar(100),function_name varchar(100))

select   'false' as success,    'the table not exists ' as message,  counter;
